		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
			<p rend="align(right)">
				<placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
				<date>August 3rd 1831</date>
			</p>
			<p>My Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I rec your letter the<lb/> reason for not <sic>gitting</sic> A the
				Day before<lb/> Because I put the letter in office<lb/> in the after noon after the
				mail was<lb/> closed. <del>(Bad cold of which I am yet not<lb/> clear I have had bad
					a cold)</del> I must<lb/> agree with you that I was wrong in leaving<lb/>
				Brandywine I got a very bad cold of which<lb/> I am yet not clear <sic>I have had
					bad a<lb/> Cold</sic> I have been at home as ever I<lb/> had I have not slept
				for 10 Days hardly<lb/> one Hour a night <sic>exept</sic> 2 nights.<lb/> I am
					<sic>realy</sic> sorry you cannot get rid of the<lb/> pain in your left side tho
				I hope by Care<lb/> and some change of air will do you good.<lb/> I am sure that
				your s is <sic>two</sic> large<lb/> for any body of weak Lungs to make the<lb/>
				people hear and not to feel hurt by it,<lb/> but if you should remain, which I
				hope<lb/> you will not do, if it injures you, you<lb/> will read the
					<sic>preyers</sic> and .<lb/> I have tried my and found that not<lb/> the Least
				care is in the , contrary,<lb/> it can hardly be heard at one yard distance<lb/> if
				you think change of air will be of<lb/> service to you, and you have not any<lb/>
				particular business in <placeName>New York</placeName>, why not<lb/> come here your
				Aunt thinks it would be</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
			<p>better for you, but do not come and run<lb/> away the same week stay 3 or 4 weeks
				by<lb/> that time you will be Quite will I hope,<lb/> I am glad that attention has
				been paid<lb/> you by many, I have nothing now but remain<lb/> D</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your affectionate uncle......</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">
				<persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName>
			</p>
			<p>Remember us Kindly to our friends<lb/> Mr &amp; <persName>Mrs. Peixotto</persName>
				our Dear friend <persName>Miss Simah<lb/> Rachel Better</persName> and the Boys and
				all the<lb/> rest of my friends in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> Tell
					<persName>Simah</persName> that all her friend here inquire<lb/> Constantly
				after her and send their love to<lb/> her/</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">To I Leeser</p>
			<p>B the <persName>Cohens</persName>
				<persName>Ettings</persName> and your Friend send<lb/> their respects to you and
				wish you better</p>
			<p>Addressed to:</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Mr <persName>Isaac Leeser</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">to the Care of A. C. Peixotto Esqr/</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">
				<placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
			</p>
		</body>
